QUEUE
=====

Queue is a collection used to hold multiple elements prior to processing.
It follows the First-In-First-Out (FIFO) principle, where the first element added to the queue is the first one to be removed.

Core Operations:
----------------
    Enqueue → add element at rear
    Dequeue → remove element from front
    Peek/Front → see first element
    isEmpty / isFull → check if queue is empty or full

Time Complexity
---------------
    Enqueue → O(1)
    Dequeue → O(1)

Common Implementations:
----------------------
    LinkedList → implements Queue interface, allows null elements
    ArrayDeque → resizable array, no capacity restrictions, faster than LinkedList for queues
    PriorityQueue → elements ordered by natural ordering or comparator, not FIFO
    ConcurrentLinkedQueue → thread-safe, non-blocking queue for concurrent access


Types of Queues:
----------------
    1. Simple Queue -  Basic FIFO
    2. Circular Queue -
       - Last position connects to first
       - Avoids wasted space in arrays
    3. Priority Queue
       - Elements processed based on priority
       - Implemented using heap